radiographic_examinations.findings: Visualized lung bases are clear. No pleural or pericardial effusion. The liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, and adrenal glands are normal. The kidneys enhance symmetrically without hydronephrosis. The small and large bowel are normal without obstruction. Appendix measures 6-7 mm with a fluid-filled portion, mildly thickened and hyperemic wall. No significant adjacent fat stranding. No evidence of extraluminal air or drainable fluid collection. Small free pelvic fluid noted. A 3.2-cm left adnexal simple cyst identified. No pathologically enlarged mesenteric or retroperitoneal lymph nodes.
